62.3	The_Battle_Hymn_of_the_Republic	The Battle Hymn of the Republic	"The Battle Hymn of the Republic" is a hymn by American writer Julia Ward Howe using the music from the song "John Brown's Body". Howe's more famous lyrics were written in November 1861 and first published in The Atlantic Monthly in February 1862. The song links the judgment of the wicked at the end of time (Torah/New Testament) with the American Civil War. Since that time it has become an extremely popular and well-known American patriotic song.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3a/The_Battle_Hymn_of_the_Republic_-_Project_Gutenberg_eText_21566.png/220px-The_Battle_Hymn_of_the_Republic_-_Project_Gutenberg_eText_21566.png
